All right Mustang,<br><br>
Good to see that your ears have stopped smoking and you are back to your usual self.<br><br>
Actually, I don't have an agent yet, as I have not much hard copy. I have been trying to read about the war and have been kept busy doing that. My dear, sweet wife has been reading from, cover to cover, a travel guide about Vietnam. When I first proposed this trip, she was very skeptical, but now enthusiastically reads me excerpts!<br><br>
I am trying to get myself prepared for the big time FLASHBACK I am bound to have - especially if I am able to hire a driver and tour my old AO in Quang Ngai province. The Internet has helped me build my own itinerary. I will spend much time in Hanoi and a beautiful place called Ha Long Bay. I will be a good tourist and spend as much time as possible in the seaside resorts!<br><br>
I think that this group on this channel has much constructive to say - especially after reading the posts of yesterday. Much good writing.<br><br>
Anyway, this site is so good that I find it impossible to not write and respond when my name is mentioned - especially when you refer to my good naturedness that extends to my habit of making sure that the toilet seat is down. I'm sure that is a given in Cookie's household. The Marines didn't teach him everything, you know.
